From: Chris Burr <christopher.burr@cern.ch>
Subject: [PATCH] fix: define _LIBCPP_DISABLE_AVAILABILITY on macOS

libc++ availability annotations reject std::to_chars (and other 13.3+
features) when targeting older macOS. A directory-level compile
definition reaches both regular compilation and the genreflex command
lines (built from each target's COMPILE_DEFINITIONS property), unlike
CXXFLAGS which genreflex/cling never sees.
---
 CMakeLists.txt | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -97,6 +97,12 @@
 # set RPATH (currently only on macOS)
 if(APPLE)
     include(cmake/GaudiRPath.cmake)
+    # conda-forge: libc++ availability annotations reject std::to_chars (and
+    # other 13.3+ features) when targeting older macOS. A directory-level
+    # compile definition reaches both regular compilation and the genreflex
+    # command lines (built from each target's COMPILE_DEFINITIONS property),
+    # unlike CXXFLAGS which genreflex/cling never sees.
+    add_compile_definitions(_LIBCPP_DISABLE_AVAILABILITY)
 endif()
 
 # Set up the GAUDI_ATOMIC_LIBS variable
